IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: LIST OF EXHIBITS CyberTip 176155219 CyberTip 138440775 NARRATIVE On 11/16/2023 the Maryland State Police Internet Crimes Against Children (ICAC) task force received CyberTip 176155219 from the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children (NCMEC). TheCyberTip, which was reported by Dropbox, was generated by the National Center for Missing andExploited Children (NCMEC), due to Dropbox reporting on 10/11/2023 at 16:30:30 UTC, they became aware a user distributed child pornography. Dropboxprovided the following information: Email Address: janifer.kevin@gmail.com (Verified 02-01-2021 14:07:52 UTC) Screen/User Name: kevin janifer ESP User ID: 3736141840 IP Address: 96.231.167.16 (Login) 04-22-2023 11:39:04 UTC Prior CyberTip: 138440775 TFC Mueller reviewed the CyberTip and observed one file of child pornography. Listed below is a description of the file. File Name: dGK4-LKcoU2Fg2GP.mp4 Description: This color video depicts a young black female, approximately 13-15 years old based on her overall size and lack of physical development, expose her breasts and her vagina in a lewd and lascivious manner. This video lasts approximately 43 seconds. height:20px; padding:0in 7px 0in 7px; width:56px" valign="top">3153845 TFC Mueller conducted a check of the login IP address and observed it to be registered to Verizon Fios and geolocate to Upper Marlboro, MD. On 11/27/2023 TFC Mueller authored a subpoena, for subscriber information pertaining to IP address 96.231.167.16, and transmitted it to the Anne Arundel County States Attorneys Office for endorsement. TFC Mueller contacted NCMEC and received the prior related CyberTip, 138440775, and upon reviewed, discovered no additional pertinent information. On 11/27/2023 TFC Mueller authored and submitted a preservation request to Dropbox for the suspects account. Case Open, investigation ongoing.

LIST OF EXHIBITS Dropbox SSW NARRATIVE On 12/20/2023 TFC Mueller submitted a SSW for the suspects Dropbox account and submitted the SSW to the Prince Georges County Circuit Court. The SSW was signed ny the Honorable Judge Coderre on the same day. On 12/27/2023 TFC Mueller submitted the SSW to Dropbox. Case Open, investigation ongoing.

LIST OF EXHIBITS Dropbox User MetaData Suspect Resume NARRATIVE On 1/2/2023 TFC Mueller received the Dropbox SSW response. TFC Mueller conducted an analysis of the response and observed the following: Total Files: 1065 Child Pornography: 3 Age Difficult: 30 TFC Mueller also observed a folder, labled Resume, which contained a picture of what appeared to be the suspects resume for a job opportunity. Within the resume, the suspects name was listed as Kevin M. Janifer and an address of 12535 Woodstock Drive East, Upper Marlboro, MD 20772 (202-280-4611), which corroborates with the Dropbox user name. TFC Mueller was able to use this information to identify the suspect as Kevin Montez Janifer (B/M DOB 4/16/2003), After review, this investigation will resolve in a knock and talk. Case Open, pending knock and talk.
